Thresholds

if ( het_r) {
  ggplot( data.frame(
    lower = apply( posterior[,,grep( 'r_lower', dimnames( posterior)[[3]])], 3, mean),
    upper = apply( posterior[,,grep( 'r_upper', dimnames( posterior)[[3]])], 3, mean))) +
    geom_histogram( aes( x = lower), fill = 'red') +
    geom_histogram( aes( x = upper), fill = 'blue') +
    geom_vline( xintercept = mean( posterior[,,grep( 'r_lower', dimnames( posterior)[[3]])]),
                color = 'darkred', linetype = 'dashed') +
    geom_vline( xintercept = mean( posterior[,,grep( 'r_upper', dimnames( posterior)[[3]])]),
                color = 'darkblue', linetype = 'dashed') +
    geom_histogram( data = data.frame( ps = as.vector( d$ps)), aes( x = ps), fill = 'grey',
                    alpha = 0.7) +
    ggtitle( 'Distribution of posterior threshold means against observed price shocks (grey)') +
    xlab( 'Price shock/threshold (scaled)') + ylab( '')
} else if ( thresholds) {
  ggplot( data.frame(
    lower = as.vector( posterior[,,'r_lower']),
    upper = as.vector( posterior[,,'r_upper']))) +
    geom_histogram( aes( x = lower), fill = 'red') +
    geom_histogram( aes( x = upper), fill = 'blue') +
    geom_vline( xintercept = mean( posterior[,,grep( 'r_lower', dimnames( posterior)[[3]])]),
                color = 'darkred', linetype = 'dashed') +
    geom_vline( xintercept = mean( posterior[,,grep( 'r_upper', dimnames( posterior)[[3]])]),
                color = 'darkblue', linetype = 'dashed') +
    geom_histogram( data = data.frame( ps = as.vector( d$ps / d$scf)), aes( x = ps), fill = 'grey',
                    alpha = 0.7, color = 'black') +
    ggtitle( 'Distribution of posterior threshold means against observed price shocks (grey)') +
    xlab( 'Price shock/threshold (scaled)') + ylab( '')
}

  mcmc_intervals( posterior[,,c( grep( 'theta_lower', dimnames( posterior)[[3]], value = T),
                                 'sigma_lower')]) +
    ggtitle( 'Lower threshold regression parameters')
}

  mcmc_intervals( posterior[,,c( grep( 'theta_upper', dimnames( posterior)[[3]], value = T),
                                 'sigma_upper')]) +
    ggtitle( 'Upper threshold regression parameters')
}

  mcmc_intervals( posterior[,,c( 'sigma_lower', 'sigma_upper')]) +
    ggtitle( 'Error variance for threshold regression')
}

Product-specific intercepts

lapply( 1:d$M, function( ii) {
  ggplot(
    apply( posterior[,,grep( paste0( 'beta_((gains)|(lpa)|(losses))\\[\\d+,', ii, '\\]'),
                             dimnames( posterior)[[3]], value = T)],
           3, mean) %>% data.frame(
             val = .,
             domain = regmatches( names( .), regexpr( '(gains)|(lpa)|(losses)', names( .))))) +
    geom_density( aes( x = val, color = domain)) +
    ggtitle( 'KDE of mean product-specific intercept by domain',
             sub = sprintf( 'Product %i', ii)) +
    xlab( 'Parameter value') + ylab( '')
})

Price elasticity

lapply( c( 'gains', 'losses'),
        function( domain) {
          mcmc_intervals( posterior[,,grep( paste0( 'delta_', domain, '\\[', d$K, ',\\d+\\]'),
                                            dimnames( posterior)[[3]], value = T)],
                          rhat = c( rep( 1, 6), rep( 1.06, 7), 1.2)) +
            ggtitle( 'Posterior distribution for price elasticity regression parameters',
                     sub = paste0( domain, ' domain')) + legend_none()
        })

Remaining parameters

lapply( 1:(d$K-1),
        function( ii) {
          lapply( if ( thresholds) c( 'gains', 'lpa', 'losses') else c( 'gains', 'losses'),
        function( domain) {
          mcmc_intervals( posterior[,,grep( paste0( 'delta_', domain, '\\[', ii, ',\\d+\\]'),
                                            dimnames( posterior)[[3]], value = T)],
                          rhat = c( rep( 1, 6), rep( 1.06, 7), 1.2)) +
            ggtitle( sprintf( 'Posterior distribution for beta %i regression parameter', ii),
                     sub = paste0( domain, ' domain')) + legend_none()
        })
        })

Subcategories

ggplot(
  data.frame( 
    id = as.factor( rep( 1:d$M, length( d$x))),
    price = do.call( c, lapply( d$x, function( y) y[,d$K]))
  )
) +
  geom_histogram( aes( x = price, fill = id), alpha = 0.7) +
  ggtitle( 'Histogram of (transformed) prices by product') +
  xlab( 'Price (transformed)') + ylab( '') +
  theme( legend.position = 'none')
